{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:luke.22",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "luke",
    "chapterNumber": 22,
    "referenceLabel": "Luke 22",
    "summary": "Source text for Luke 22 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:1",
      "text": "Now the feast of Unleavened Bread drew near, which is called the Passover.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:2",
      "text": "And the chief priests and the scribes were seeking how to put him to death; for they feared the people.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:3",
      "text": "Then Satan entered into Judas called Iscariot, who was of the number of the twelve;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:4",
      "text": "he went away and conferred with the chief priests and officers how he might betray him to them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:5",
      "text": "And they were glad, and engaged to give him money.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:6",
      "text": "So he agreed, and sought an opportunity to betray him to them in the absence of the multitude.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:7",
      "text": "Then came the day of Unleavened Bread, on which the passover lamb had to be sacrificed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:8",
      "text": "So Jesus sent Peter and John, saying, “Go and prepare the passover for us, that we may eat it.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:9",
      "text": "They said to him, “Where will you have us prepare it?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:10",
      "text": "He said to them, “Behold, when you have entered the city, a man carrying a jar of water will meet you; follow him into the house which he enters,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:11",
      "text": "and tell the householder, ‘The Teacher says to you, Where is the guest room, where I am to eat the passover with my disciples?’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:12",
      "text": "And he will show you a large upper room furnished; there make ready.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:13",
      "text": "And they went, and found it as he had told them; and they prepared the passover.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:14",
      "text": "And when the hour came, he sat at table, and the apostles with him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:15",
      "text": "And he said to them, “I have earnestly desired to eat this passover with you before I suffer;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:16",
      "text": "for I tell you I shall not eat it until it is fulfilled in the kingdom of God.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:17",
      "text": "And he took a cup, and when he had given thanks he said, “Take this, and divide it among yourselves;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:18",
      "text": "for I tell you that from now on I shall not drink of the fruit of the vine until the kingdom of God comes.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:19",
      "text": "And he took bread, and when he had given thanks he broke it and gave it to them, saying, “This is my body which is given for you. Do this in remembrance of me.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:20",
      "text": "And likewise the cup after supper, saying, “This cup which is poured out for you is the new covenant in my blood.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:21",
      "text": "But behold the hand of him who betrays me is with me on the table.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:22",
      "text": "For the Son of man goes as it has been determined; but woe to that man by whom he is betrayed!”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:23",
      "text": "And they began to question one another, which of them it was that would do this.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:24",
      "text": "A dispute also arose among them, which of them was to be regarded as the greatest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:25",
      "text": "And he said to them, “The kings of the Gentiles exercise lordship over them; and those in authority over them are called benefactors.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:26",
      "text": "But not so with you; rather let the greatest among you become as the youngest, and the leader as one who serves.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:27",
      "text": "For which is the greater, one who sits at table, or one who serves? Is it not the one who sits at table? But I am among you as one who serves.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:28",
      "text": "“You are those who have continued with me in my trials;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:29",
      "text": "and I assign to you, as my Father assigned to me, a kingdom,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:30",
      "text": "that you may eat and drink at my table in my kingdom, and sit on thrones judging the twelve tribes of Israel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:31",
      "text": "“Simon, Simon, behold, Satan demanded to have you, that he might sift you like wheat,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.32",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:32",
      "text": "but I have prayed for you that your faith may not fail; and when you have turned again, strengthen your brethren.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.33",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:33",
      "text": "And he said to him, “Lord, I am ready to go with you to prison and to death.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.34",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:34",
      "text": "He said, “I tell you, Peter, the cock will not crow this day, until you three times deny that you know me.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.35",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:35",
      "text": "And he said to them, “When I sent you out with no purse or bag or sandals, did you lack anything?” They said, “Nothing.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.36",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:36",
      "text": "He said to them, “But now, let him who has a purse take it, and likewise a bag. And let him who has no sword sell his mantle and buy one.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.37",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:37",
      "text": "For I tell you that this scripture must be fulfilled in me, ‘And he was reckoned with transgressors’; for what is written about me has its fulfilment.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.38",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:38",
      "text": "And they said, “Look, Lord, here are two swords.” And he said to them, “It is enough.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.39",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:39",
      "text": "And he came out, and went, as was his custom, to the Mount of Olives; and the disciples followed him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.40",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:40",
      "text": "And when he came to the place he said to them, “Pray that you may not enter into temptation.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.41",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:41",
      "text": "And he withdrew from them about a stone's throw, and knelt down and prayed,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.42",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:42",
      "text": "“Father, if thou art willing, remove this cup from me; nevertheless not my will, but thine, be done.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.45",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 45,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:45",
      "text": "And when he rose from prayer, he came to the disciples and found them sleeping for sorrow,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.46",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 46,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:46",
      "text": "and he said to them, “Why do you sleep? Rise and pray that you may not enter into temptation.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.47",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 47,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:47",
      "text": "While he was still speaking, there came a crowd, and the man called Judas, one of the twelve, was leading them. He drew near to Jesus to kiss him;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.48",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 48,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:48",
      "text": "but Jesus said to him, “Judas, would you betray the Son of man with a kiss?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.49",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 49,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:49",
      "text": "And when those who were about him saw what would follow, they said, “Lord, shall we strike with the sword?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.50",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 50,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:50",
      "text": "And one of them struck the slave of the high priest and cut off his right ear.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.51",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 51,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:51",
      "text": "But Jesus said, “No more of this!” And he touched his ear and healed him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.52",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 52,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:52",
      "text": "Then Jesus said to the chief priests and officers of the temple and elders, who had come out against him, “Have you come out as against a robber, with swords and clubs?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.53",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 53,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:53",
      "text": "When I was with you day after day in the temple, you did not lay hands on me. But this is your hour, and the power of darkness.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.54",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 54,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:54",
      "text": "Then they seized him and led him away, bringing him into the high priest's house. Peter followed at a distance;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.55",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 55,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:55",
      "text": "and when they had kindled a fire in the middle of the courtyard and sat down together, Peter sat among them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.56",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 56,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:56",
      "text": "Then a maid, seeing him as he sat in the light and gazing at him, said, “This man also was with him.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.57",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 57,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:57",
      "text": "But he denied it, saying, “Woman, I do not know him.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.58",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 58,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:58",
      "text": "And a little later some one else saw him and said, “You also are one of them.” But Peter said, “Man, I am not.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.59",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 59,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:59",
      "text": "And after an interval of about an hour still another insisted, saying, “Certainly this man also was with him; for he is a Galilean.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.60",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 60,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:60",
      "text": "But Peter said, “Man, I do not know what you are saying.” And immediately, while he was still speaking, the cock crowed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.61",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 61,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:61",
      "text": "And the Lord turned and looked at Peter. And Peter remembered the word of the Lord, how he had said to him, “Before the cock crows today, you will deny me three times.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.62",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 62,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:62",
      "text": "And he went out and wept bitterly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.63",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 63,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:63",
      "text": "Now the men who were holding Jesus mocked him and beat him;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.64",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 64,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:64",
      "text": "they also blindfolded him and asked him, “Prophesy! Who is it that struck you?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.65",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 65,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:65",
      "text": "And they spoke many other words against him, reviling him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.66",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 66,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:66",
      "text": "When day came, the assembly of the elders of the people gathered together, both chief priests and scribes; and they led him away to their council, and they said,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.67",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 67,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:67",
      "text": "“If you are the Christ, tell us.” But he said to them, “If I tell you, you will not believe;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.68",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 68,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:68",
      "text": "and if I ask you, you will not answer.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.69",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 69,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:69",
      "text": "But from now on the Son of man shall be seated at the right hand of the power of God.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:luke.22.70",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "luke",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 70,
      "referenceLabel": "Luke 22:70",
      "text": "And they all said, “Are you the Son of God, then?” And he said to them, “You say that I am.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
